<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=news_announcements&message.id=87" target="_blank" class="postlink">Moorgard Post on Patch Issues:</a></span> &lt;---LINK
<br />

<br />
There are several issues with today's update that are negatively affecting gameplay. Here are some of the key issues that our team is focused on right now, with the status of their resolution:
<br />
Tradeskill zones crashing. We are investigating the cause. If you have information on how to consistently make a crash happen, please feel free to pass it directly to me via PM. 
<br />
Certain zones being down when players attempt to enter them. We are briefly bouncing all servers to take care of this issue. The zones in question should be accessible very soon. 
<br />
Missing character art at certain LOD settings. We have found the problem and are in the process of correcting it. 
<br />
Some quests being reset to the beginning, even if completed. The cause has been found and fixed. See specifics below.
<br />
Our plan is that as soon as all these issues are confirmed to be fixed, we will do another update. Since the amount of data needed to be pushed is relatively small, we don't anticipate longer than a 45 to 60 minute downtime.
<br />

<br />
We'll update you again when we have a better idea of the timeframe of the update. Thanks for your patience.
<br />

<br />
The quests that have been reset by today's bug are listed below. If your character has any of these quests in any stage in the quest journal, they will be reset to the beginning if you log in before the fix is applied. After the fix, characters logging in will be unaffected, but unfortunately we will NOT be able to retroactively fix characters that have been affected. We sincerely apologize to those for whom this will be the case.
<br />

<br />
If you have advanced in any of the quests below and do not want to lose progress on them, we STRONGLY encourage you not to log in until our next update is complete. Again, if you log in before the fix is applied we will not be able to reset your progress to where it was before.
<br />

<br />
If you have previously completed any of these quests, you will find that they have been moved to your active page and reset to the beginning. When we apply the fix for this bug, quests you have already completed will be moved back to the Completed tab of your journal. There is no need to delete them at this time.
<br />

<br />
Zarvonn's Legacy 
<br />
Rings that Thirst 
